[GDS-Poitou-Charentes, the animal health protection group of Poitou-Charentes, is an association of breeders from 4 Departments (out of metropolitan France's 96 departments), located in West France (Charente, Charente-Maritime, Deux-SÃ¨vres, and Vienne).

The blindness in newborn calves, followed by their death within a few days, may be indicative of other congenital brain changes. They may be discovered, or excluded, if/when brains are subject to full-scale PM examinations, addressing gross- and histopathological changes. Congenital CNS changes in progeny of BTV-8 infected dams were reported during the major event in western Europe, 2006-2008. (https://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/epdf/10.1111/j.1865-1682.2008.01034.x).

Additional details from field and laboratory will be useful.

It will be interesting to note if similar cases have been observed recently in the other countries which have been experiencing BTV-8 circulation and infection, namely Switzerland and Germany.

Hopefully, sufficient quantities of the killed BTV-8 vaccine are kept available in stock in the affected and at-risk countries.

HealthMap/ProMED-mail map of France: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=6316637,34201.

Footnote: in the circulated version of our previous BTV-8 posting, 20190201.6290247, the start of the (Swiss) event and its confirmation were given as 19 Oct 2018 and 23 Oct 2018; the correct dates were 19 Oct 2017 and 23 Oct 2017, respectively. This mistake has already been corrected in the website version. - Mod.AS]
